  "name": "Adrian Sina",
  "profile": "Romanian Dance DJ & producer\r\nStarted DJing in a club at 16, ran his own radio show at 18. Produced some songs on the first album of [a=Akcent], Romanian band he has been a member of ever since.\r\nIn 2008, Adrian opened his own recording studio [l=SisterHoodLive Records], composing and producing [a=Akcent]'s album \"Fara Lacrimi\" (\"No Tears\").\r\nIn 2009 he takes his career a step further with two new projects [a=Roller Sis] and [a=Vivien O'Hara].\r\n2010 brought a new Sina hit, this time a collaboration with [a=Andreea Banica], \"Love in Brasil\". This has also been the year that Adrian became a complete artist, launching his first solo project.\r\n",
